1
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:29,400
PHRA NAKHON
DURING THE SECOND WORLD WAR

2
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:32,720
<i>This diamond necklace</i>
<i>belongs to Lady Sihayothin.</i>

3
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:35,680
The next item is a bracelet

4
00:00:35,760 --> 00:00:38,520
crafted by Lord Vijitsilp,

5
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:40,800
a one-of-a-kind piece.

6
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:41,840
This bracelet

7
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:44,440
starts at 500 baht.

8
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:47,640
It's quite rare.

9
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:50,600
I heard Lord Vijitsilp made it himself

10
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,760
as a gift for his wife.

11
00:00:57,560 --> 00:00:58,760
One thousand baht.

12
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:00,280
One thousand there.

13
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:03,160
The current bid is 1,000 baht.

14
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:05,640
Is anyone else interested?

15
00:01:06,160 --> 00:01:07,440
One thousand one hundred baht.

16
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:09,320
One thousand one hundred baht!

17
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,880
One thousand two hundred baht.

18
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:12,800
One thousand three hundred baht.

19
00:01:14,520 --> 00:01:15,960
Two thousand.

20
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:18,440
Two thousand over there!

21
00:01:18,520 --> 00:01:20,280
Two thousand baht.

22
00:01:20,360 --> 00:01:22,280
Two thousand baht.

23
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:24,920
The current bid is 2,000 baht.

24
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:27,360
Two thousand five hundred baht.

25
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,720
Two thousand five hundred baht.

26
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:33,440
Hey, Thatri.

27
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:36,000
Won't this just be a slap in the face
to Mr. Sathit?

28
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:38,920
But I wanted to get it for Sasi.

29
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:44,520
Three thousand baht.

30
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:45,960
Four thousand.

31
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:48,120
Five thousand baht.

32
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:50,840
Ten thousand.

33
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:01,520
Kajorn.

34
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,480
Kajorn…

35
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,520
- How've you been?
- I've been good.

36
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:10,360
It's been a while. You both look lovely.

37
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:12,000
Should we?

38
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:12,960
Of course.

39
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:19,120
YOU ARE CORDIALLY INVITED
MR. KAJORN PITAKTHIN

40
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,160
The bracelet of Lord Vijitsilp

41
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:35,200
goes to Mr. Thatri

42
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,080
Thatripan.

43
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:56,320
Excuse me, madam. May I have
your invitation card, please?

44
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,400
Uh…

45
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:00,000
Do you not have an invitation card, madam?

46
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:02,760
Of course, I do. My friend has it.

47
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,080
I'm waiting for her right now.

48
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:05,600
Yes, madam.

49
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,320
Srichan.

50
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:22,640
I never knew you liked
collecting jewelry, Tri.

51
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:25,080
I thought you were only
into outdoor activities.

52
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:29,360
It's not that strange, is it?

53
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:33,560
It is, because I know

54
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,960
everything there is to know about you.

55
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:39,760
Inside…

56
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:41,520
and out.

57
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:43,480
- Ooh.
- Whoa.

58
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,280
I think

59
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:49,000
we need to rekindle our relationship.

60
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:51,640
You can't do this.

61
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:54,520
Why not?

62
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,400
Because you are my wife.

63
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,120
Poj…

64
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:08,040
Didn't you say you weren't coming?

65
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:09,800
If I hadn't come,

66
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:13,720
would I have caught you flirting
with this fool in front of everyone here?

67
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:17,640
We weren't flirting.

68
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,920
I haven't done anything.

69
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:24,600
I've done worse than this.

70
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:29,080
Let me tell you, Poj.
If you're still being this stingy

71
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:31,640
and refuse to get me
that vacation home in Hua Hin,

72
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:35,640
I'll gather all of Bangkok
to watch me and Tri…

73
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:37,000
putting on a show.

74
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,760
It'll have them spitting!

75
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:42,200
- You're dead, boy!
- Hold up.

76
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,120
Why am I involved?

77
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,360
Not involved, you say?

78
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,320
- You're dead!
- Ah!

79
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:51,640
Poj!

80
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:56,680
Are you just going to stand there
like a statue? Go get him!

81
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:03,280
- Hey!
- Stop!

82
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,760
- Get him.
- Hey.

83
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,640
Are you alright, sir?

84
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:49,120
Go get him!

85
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:51,160
Let's go! Come on!

86
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,880
- Ouch!
- Oh!

87
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,520
- I'm sorry. Are you alright?
- Ouch…

88
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:03,640
Watch where you're going. Can't you see?

89
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:06,840
You weren't looking either.
Otherwise, you would've seen me coming.

90
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,360
You…

91
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:09,920
You were the one who ran into me.

92
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,760
I was rushing into the party,
that's why I didn't see you.

93
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:15,440
Then why not use the front?
Why sneak in through the back?

94
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:20,480
Ah, I get it now.

95
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,680
Trying to sneak into the party?

96
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:24,600
I see women like you all the time.

97
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,960
Plenty of them chase after me, too.

98
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,480
Let me tell you,

99
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:30,000
for a lady of your stature,
chasing after a man like this

100
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:30,920
isn't very becoming.

101
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:34,360
I'm not chasing you.
Don't be so full of yourself.

102
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:39,000
- Ugh!
- Hey, you!

103
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,800
Rajit.

104
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:58,440
Keep it down, please.

105
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,200
You're embarrassing me.

106
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:09,120
I'm just so angry.

107
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,320
What kind of man is he?

108
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:13,760
Rude, full of himself,
he has absolutely no manners!

109
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:17,280
Enough now.

110
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,360
Tell me, Rajit,

111
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:22,000
why did you follow me to the party?

112
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:26,760
We see each other every time
you're in Bangkok anyway, don't we?

113
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,040
Out with it, now.

114
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:34,960
Well, all the women there

115
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:37,440
were so elegant and wealthy.

116
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,920
Don't tell me you're jealous, Rajit?

117
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:45,480
I was just concerned.

118
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:50,040
Concerned or jealous? Be honest.

119
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,440
Rajit…

120
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,240
We are lovers.

121
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:03,320
Lovers must trust each other.
You need to trust me.

122
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:12,200
I know. I'm sorry.

123
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:13,280
It's okay.

124
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,920
When are you heading back to Penang?

125
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,560
Tomorrow.

126
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,640
I feel bad for bothering Suda.

127
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:22,040
I've been staying with her
for so many days now.

128
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,240
In that case, let me see you off tomorrow.

129
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,240
That'd be nice.

130
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:34,799
As soon as I reach Penang,

131
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:37,280
I'll send a telegram.

132
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,720
Just write me a letter.
Telegrams are too expensive.

133
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,080
I'll leave you to board the ship.

134
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:48,000
I must get back to work.

135
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:55,040
Have a safe trip. I'm off.

136
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,680
Today's a holiday.

137
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:15,000
Where would he be going to work?

138
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,960
Don't be like that, darling.

139
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:49,480
I just had to attend
to my "beloved" first.

140
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:50,680
Once I was finished,

141
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,040
I'm back with you now, aren't I?

142
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,880
Why bother coming back?

143
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:57,200
Why didn't you just follow her to Penang?

144
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,200
Kajorn…

145
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:16,920
Suda…

146
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:19,640
Rajit?

147
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:21,400
I thought you were boarding the ship.

148
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:24,080
Can you stop being so dim-witted?

149
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:26,520
If you have nothing sensible to say,

150
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,960
then just tell me the truth.

151
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:39,680
Kajorn and I love each other.

152
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,280
That's the truth you wanted to hear.

153
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:50,120
So you conspired to deceive me?

154
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,040
The man I love…

155
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:55,600
and my dearest friend?

156
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:58,560
How could you do this?

157
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:00,640
Do you feel absolutely no remorse?

158
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:06,040
Love doesn't leave room for three.

159
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,880
Kajorn chose me,

160
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:13,520
and I love him.

161
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,640
This was inevitable.

162
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:20,200
So you lied to my face,

163
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,520
playing me for a fool?

164
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:24,640
Is that it, Kajorn?

165
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:26,960
Because you're acting this way.

166
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:30,200
This is why I didn't tell you.
I was afraid you'd lash out

167
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:31,560
and make things worse.

168
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:33,760
But I intended to tell you

169
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,960
after you graduated.

170
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:37,560
Well, I'm glad.

171
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,360
I'm glad you said that.

172
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:42,520
Now I know for certain,

173
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:45,400
you aren't worth
a single moment of my regret.

174
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:50,120
As for you, Suda.

175
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:53,360
If only you'd been honest
with me from the start,

176
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:55,280
I would've stepped aside.

177
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:59,400
To me, our friendship

178
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:03,360
was worth far more
than a two-timing man like him.

179
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:06,120
But the thing that kills me is…

180
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:10,000
you stabbed me in the back.

181
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,760
I'm in love with Kajorn.

182
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:20,680
I chose him over our friendship.

183
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:24,560
Hate me if you want,

184
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:26,480
but I had to do what I had to do.

185
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,320
Go home, Rajit.

186
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:35,120
This place has no space
for a third wheel like you.

187
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,480
Oh, I'm leaving.

188
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:46,200
But before I go,

189
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,960
I'm going to make sure
I'm compensated for this betrayal.

190
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:55,080
Hey, Rajit!

191
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,720
Consider that your payment.

192
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,640
It's hardly enough,

193
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:05,840
but I suppose I'll take it as a loss.

194
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:15,120
THATRIPAN RESIDENCE

195
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:19,320
Do you like it, Sasi?

196
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,080
I love it.

197
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:27,960
But 10,000 baht? That's far too expensive.

198
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:31,680
If you keep being this extravagant
just to please me,

199
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:34,160
I won't speak to you anymore.

200
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:35,880
Oh, come now.

201
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,960
This is a gift to celebrate
one year of our engagement.

202
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,080
It's just a small amount.

203
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,360
Don't be angry with me.

204
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,560
Tri…

205
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:52,840
My mother is eager for us to marry.

206
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:55,200
How do you feel about that?

207
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,600
I'd marry you tomorrow if I could.

208
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,120
But if we marry,

209
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:04,000
will you still be out
at social events every night

210
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:07,200
and vanish into the jungle
for months on end as you are now?

211
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,040
What's wrong with that?

212
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,840
I attend these functions

213
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:13,720
to build connections.

214
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,680
Everything I manage, from the store

215
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:19,200
to the markets

216
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:21,400
and the stables, is running perfectly.

217
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:24,240
Why so serious about it?

218
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:28,120
Never mind. Let's change the subject.

219
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,320
I heard

220
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:34,000
you outbid Mr. Sathit for this bracelet.

221
00:15:34,680 --> 00:15:36,960
Isn't that just asking for trouble?

222
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,360
That bloodsucking merchant?

223
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:42,560
I've never liked the man.

224
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:44,880
Even if we are enemies,

225
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:47,280
a man like that is no match for me.

226
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:52,480
Thatri, you son of a bitch.

227
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:54,560
Just because you were born rich

228
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:58,040
and into a noble family,
you think you can just step all over me?

229
00:15:58,120 --> 00:15:59,760
One day,

230
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:02,080
I'll make you crawl to my feet and beg.

231
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:05,080
I've despised you forever.

232
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:07,360
Ever since you kept the rice prices down

233
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:09,000
during the war.

234
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:11,760
Everyone knows you're supposed
to jack up the prices to profit!

235
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:14,000
We need to hit him where it hurts, boss.

236
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,640
Force him out of the rice business.

237
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:18,400
Forcing him to stop won't be easy.

238
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:27,000
Why must I stock such frivolous goods?

239
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,840
Can we expect them to sell
in times like these?

240
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:30,560
I think

241
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:33,680
there are still plenty of people
who aren't suffering.

242
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:36,040
They're more than willing to pay.

243
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,400
Imported spirits,

244
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:40,040
fine teas, coffee, or quality garments.

245
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:42,480
They'll fly off the shelves,
I guarantee it.

246
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:45,160
But it requires a massive investment.

247
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:47,200
I don't think the risk is worth taking.

248
00:16:47,280 --> 00:16:49,320
- About the risk--
- I don't want such trouble.

249
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:51,440
I am content as things are.

250
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:02,640
Bah!

251
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:04,240
Acting all humble?

252
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:06,200
Fine.

253
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,119
I don't believe

254
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:11,200
that I can't corrupt you with greed,

255
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,319
Thatri.

256
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:15,800
Two million for the investment?

257
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:16,640
THATRIPAN STABLES

258
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,839
You must be joking, Nop.

259
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:20,079
I'm dead serious.

260
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:23,040
Everyone's dying to get their hands
on imported goods.

261
00:17:23,119 --> 00:17:25,520
I've got hundreds
lining up with deposits ready.

262
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:28,480
At least two million in total.

263
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:31,000
All we need is someone
to bring the goods in.

264
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:34,640
And why me? There are plenty
of other merchants out there.

265
00:17:35,840 --> 00:17:38,240
Because nobody
has the spare cash like you do.

266
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:39,480
Tri.

267
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,520
Think about it.

268
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:45,720
You're already selling staples,
like rice and oil, at a loss.

269
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:48,800
Making a profit on luxury goods

270
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,560
won't hurt anyone.

271
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:53,200
It's not like you're hurting the poor.

272
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:56,000
Why wouldn't you take it?
It's an easy profit.

273
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:04,640
ELIZABETH HOTEL

274
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,400
Mr. Thatri.

275
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:10,480
I heard your shipment
has finally arrived, has it?

276
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:13,520
News travels fast.

277
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:15,640
It arrived only this morning.

278
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,880
A businessman must stay informed.

279
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,760
But you've taken quite a gamble.

280
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,720
Accepting unlimited deposits?

281
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:26,600
If you fail to deliver those goods,

282
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:29,200
the penalties alone
would leave you bankrupt, wouldn't they?

283
00:18:32,120 --> 00:18:34,440
And why would I fail to deliver?

284
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:36,080
The goods are already here.

285
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:37,880
It's just speculation.

286
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:40,080
If you'll excuse me.

287
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:56,800
<i>We interrupt you with breaking news.</i>

288
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:58,760
<i>A massive fire has broken out</i>

289
00:18:58,840 --> 00:19:00,800
<i>at Warehouse Nine, Khlong Toei Port.</i>

290
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:04,000
<i>The blaze is spreading rapidly,</i>
<i>causing extensive damage.</i>

291
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:06,000
<i>Emergency services</i>
<i>are currently on the scene,</i>

292
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,840
<i>working to contain the fire.</i>

293
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:09,520
<i>The area has been sealed off,</i>

294
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:13,400
<i>and residents in the vicinity</i>
<i>are urged to evacuate immediately.</i>

295
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:52,920
Sir, you are not allowed in.

296
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,080
Entry is not permitted.

297
00:19:58,080 --> 00:19:59,240
Contain the fire.

298
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:10,160
INFERNO RAVAGES WAREHOUSE
MILLIONS IN LOSSES

299
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:13,680
NOTHING BUT ASH
MASSIVE STOCK INCINERATED

300
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:15,320
YOUNG TYCOON BANKRUPTED

301
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:17,880
YOUNG TYCOON'S SUDDEN BANKRUPTCY
FROM HERO TO ZERO

302
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:33,960
Father…

303
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:37,160
Mother…

304
00:20:40,360 --> 00:20:41,520
I'm sorry.

305
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:52,120
Sorry I couldn't take care
of the inheritance

306
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,360
as I promised.

307
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:34,600
THATRIPAN STABLES

308
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:36,040
These stables have been with me for ages,

309
00:21:36,120 --> 00:21:37,640
since my father's time.

310
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:40,200
It's hard

311
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:42,880
to let them go.

312
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:48,200
Let it go, man.

313
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:50,680
At least you'll have enough
to pay off some of your debts.

314
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:54,640
Thanks, Nop.

315
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:56,280
Finding a buyer couldn't have been easy.

316
00:21:57,680 --> 00:22:00,040
It's the least I could do, buddy.

317
00:22:03,080 --> 00:22:04,360
When's the buyer getting here?

318
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:07,800
Mr. Pranop.

319
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:14,400
Mr. Thatri.

320
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:16,200
We were just expecting you, sir.

321
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:19,560
Sorry, I've been here for a while.

322
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:21,120
Just looking over the place.

323
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:23,880
After all, I'm going to be
the new owner soon.

324
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,080
Don't tell me

325
00:22:25,160 --> 00:22:27,520
you're the one who brought him
to buy my stables?

326
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,400
You know how I feel about him.

327
00:22:33,120 --> 00:22:35,640
I'm not selling
to someone like you. Leave.

328
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:39,840
Stop acting like a child, Tri.

329
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,520
We already had a deal.

330
00:22:43,160 --> 00:22:44,040
You have no idea.

331
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:46,560
My imported shipment

332
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:48,800
arrived only a few hours
before it burned down.

333
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:51,600
And the very next day,
his market is flooded

334
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:52,880
with the exact same items.

335
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:56,520
That's fine.

336
00:22:57,520 --> 00:22:59,560
Just have him return my deposit.

337
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:03,480
Well, Tri?

338
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:05,480
Can you return the money?

339
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:09,120
I don't think so.

340
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:12,240
You've already blown
the deposit on your debts.

341
00:23:12,320 --> 00:23:15,400
You're even desperate enough
to sell your house.

342
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:18,120
Don't be a fool, my dear friend.

343
00:23:20,280 --> 00:23:21,400
Why would you say that?

344
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,560
You were the one
who pushed me to take this order.

345
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:34,720
I thought he was untouchable.

346
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:37,080
Turns out, he's just
as greedy as the rest of us.

347
00:23:38,520 --> 00:23:41,120
If I hadn't played
the part of the loyal friend,

348
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:43,440
this wouldn't have been half as easy.

349
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,760
Don't forget my share, sir.

350
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:47,200
Don't you worry about that.

351
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:51,760
I almost pity Thatri

352
00:23:52,360 --> 00:23:53,960
for having a best friend like you.

353
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:59,760
Worry about yourself, sir.
I still don't see

354
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:02,440
how tricking him
into importing those goods

355
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:04,440
is going to bankrupt him.

356
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:06,000
Just wait and see.

357
00:24:06,080 --> 00:24:08,680
Once that shipment arrives,

358
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:11,040
his life will fall into the gutter.

359
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:16,960
You were with him, weren't you?

360
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:19,760
Hey!

361
00:24:19,840 --> 00:24:22,040
You better have proof for that.

362
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:23,800
Even if we are friends,

363
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:25,800
I can still take you to court.

364
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:29,640
Tri!

365
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:30,840
Hey.

366
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,320
What have I ever done to you?

367
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:35,760
How could you do this to me?

368
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:37,280
Because I loathe you.

369
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:38,560
Is that enough?

370
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:40,080
Bah!

371
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:41,920
You think you're so high and mighty?

372
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:44,040
You're just as greedy as the rest of us.

373
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:46,280
I may have laid the trap,

374
00:24:46,360 --> 00:24:48,080
but if you were not greedy,

375
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,960
would you have walked
right into it yourself?

376
00:24:53,840 --> 00:24:55,560
If you want to blame someone,

377
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:58,680
blame your own greed and stupidity.

378
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:07,440
Come on!

379
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:10,600
Kill him!

380
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:24,960
Hey.

381
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:56,640
So much for all that pride
and arrogance, huh?

382
00:26:59,120 --> 00:27:01,360
Let me put you out of your misery.

383
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:10,320
Charnnarong…

384
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:13,800
Let's get out of here.

385
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:37,960
Thank you, sir.

386
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:41,960
If not for you, I wouldn't have survived.

387
00:27:44,280 --> 00:27:46,920
If not for your help
when I was in exile abroad,

388
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:50,120
my family would have suffered greatly.

389
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:53,760
What will you do next?

390
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:56,920
I must return the deposits

391
00:27:57,000 --> 00:28:00,040
and pay the penalties
to every customer who placed an order.

392
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:04,760
As for the rest,

393
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:07,440
I'll treat it as a lesson.

394
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:10,560
If you do that,

395
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:12,600
you'll be left with almost nothing.

396
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,360
It is necessary, sir.

397
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:16,840
The honor of the Thatripan name

398
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:19,360
is the only thing I have left to protect.

399
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:24,360
I will not allow anyone
to tarnish the name of my parents.

400
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:34,640
Should you ever need help,
just say the word.

401
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:37,560
Oh,

402
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:39,640
I heard you have a fiancée.

403
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:44,240
If the wedding plans hit any snags,
do let me know.

404
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:48,160
Thank you, sir.

405
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:52,160
But I have full faith in Sasi.

406
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:55,280
No matter what happens,

407
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:58,240
I know she'll stand by my side.

408
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:10,840
I want you to break off the engagement.

409
00:29:21,280 --> 00:29:22,880
Mother, please. I think--

410
00:29:31,800 --> 00:29:35,040
If you truly love her,
you'll understand my position.

411
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:38,000
I simply cannot allow her
to suffer in poverty.

412
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:45,120
And you, Sasi?

413
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:47,160
What do you think?

414
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:54,840
I'm so sorry, Tri.

415
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:58,520
I'm just so sorry.

416
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:02,760
She's my only daughter.

417
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:06,280
Her happiness is everything to me.

418
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:08,640
If you cannot provide for her,

419
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:10,400
- then I must--
- I understand.

420
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:15,280
I know

421
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:17,360
this seems heartless,

422
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:19,880
but I will do anything for my daughter.

423
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:22,160
If you have any anger, direct it at me.

424
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:25,520
I am willing to kneel
and beg for your forgiveness myself.

425
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:27,280
No, please.

426
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:39,400
I'll let her go.

427
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:07,520
PENANG

428
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:10,680
My goodness, that exam was brutal.

429
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:12,920
How did you do, Nareewan?

430
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:15,720
With my level,
just passing would be a miracle.

431
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:19,120
Tell me about it.

432
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:20,440
How about you, Rajit?

433
00:31:20,520 --> 00:31:23,120
Oh, don't even bother asking her.

434
00:31:23,200 --> 00:31:24,360
She's always the top student.

435
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:26,800
I wouldn't go that far.

436
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:28,680
I shouldn't have asked.

437
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:31,920
Vijarn.

438
00:31:41,840 --> 00:31:45,960
After my exams, I planned to go home
to take care of my grandfather.

439
00:31:47,720 --> 00:31:49,360
I can't believe he's gone.

440
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:53,840
He had been in poor health
for quite a while.

441
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:55,680
At least he is at peace now.

442
00:31:58,240 --> 00:31:59,920
Try to stay strong, Ms. Rajit.

443
00:32:07,320 --> 00:32:08,280
And this…

444
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:11,360
These are the wishes left by Mr. Som.

445
00:32:19,080 --> 00:32:20,440
Once your studies are concluded,

446
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:22,680
you must return to Phuket

447
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:24,440
to claim your inheritance.

448
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:28,120
What? Claim my inheritance?

449
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:39,640
I, MR. SOM ADISUAN, HEREBY DELACRE
THAT I AM OF SOUND MIND AND MEMORY

450
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,840
This is an enormous fortune.

451
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:45,200
Why would he leave all this to me?

452
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:48,800
What will Aunt Paetai, Aunt Fuangfah,

453
00:32:48,880 --> 00:32:51,840
and the rest of the family say?

454
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:53,800
Please, set your mind at ease.

455
00:32:53,880 --> 00:32:55,680
By bloodline,

456
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:57,560
you are the closest relative.

457
00:32:58,280 --> 00:33:01,280
The other relatives
have no legal claim to this.

458
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:06,320
But you are not the sole heir.

459
00:33:07,520 --> 00:33:09,160
Please, look through
the remaining documents.

460
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:19,800
MR. THATRI VORAPAT

461
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:22,000
Who is he?

462
00:33:22,080 --> 00:33:24,560
He is the child of Mr. Som's other sister.

463
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:26,320
He is your uncle by relation,

464
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:29,640
and he is to receive
the other half of the fortune.

465
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:34,240
MR. THATRI VORAPAT

466
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,000
Uncle Tri?

467
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:45,120
<i>To my dearest Rajit, I am so sorry.</i>

468
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:48,040
<i>All these years, I let your mother suffer.</i>

469
00:33:49,120 --> 00:33:51,480
<i>When I inherited the wealth</i>
<i>from your great-grandfather,</i>

470
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:54,040
<i>I was too selfish</i>
<i>to share it with my siblings.</i>

471
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:56,440
<i>After your mother passed,</i>

472
00:33:56,520 --> 00:33:58,360
<i>I was consumed by guilt.</i>

473
00:33:58,440 --> 00:34:01,840
<i>Even though I have cared</i>
<i>for you all these years,</i>

474
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:05,400
<i>it could never compensate</i>
<i>for the wrong I have done.</i>

475
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,280
<i>I am entrusting</i>

476
00:34:07,840 --> 00:34:09,000
<i>my fortune to you,</i>

477
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:12,639
<i>alongside the son</i>
<i>of my other sister, Suang,</i>

478
00:34:12,719 --> 00:34:14,719
<i>as a way to make amends</i>
<i>for all my failures.</i>

479
00:34:15,960 --> 00:34:18,000
<i>Please, forgive me.</i>

480
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:19,800
<i>Signed, Grandfather Som.</i>

481
00:34:22,239 --> 00:34:23,639
Grandfather…

482
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:56,760
Tri! Over here!

483
00:35:56,840 --> 00:35:57,920
Ahh.

484
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:00,480
Wait.

485
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:04,840
Srichan, why do you have luggage?

486
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:08,560
We only met so you could pay me
for the restaurant shares

487
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:10,400
that I sold you, right?

488
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:12,160
That's right.

489
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:17,160
Here you go. The payment for your shares.

490
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:19,800
Thank you.

491
00:36:24,560 --> 00:36:27,680
But why did you suggest
meeting at Bangkok Noi Station?

492
00:36:27,760 --> 00:36:30,280
I'm heading to Chiang Mai.
This is the Southern Line.

493
00:36:31,640 --> 00:36:33,440
I had to be strategic.

494
00:36:34,040 --> 00:36:35,840
Everyone knows you're heading North,

495
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:38,240
so I arranged to meet you in the South.

496
00:36:38,320 --> 00:36:41,200
No one will find us here.
Aren't I brilliant?

497
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:43,640
Why would you do that?

498
00:36:45,080 --> 00:36:47,720
Wherever you go, I go.

499
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:50,240
I'm sick of that old man.

500
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:55,760
So… how about we relive

501
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:57,960
our good old days in London?

502
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:00,800
You're a married woman.
Have some respect for Mr. Poj.

503
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:02,080
Ugh, Tri.

504
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:03,200
You!

505
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:07,080
You're running off with my wife

506
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:09,560
and helping her steal my money?

507
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:11,520
- You're a dead man!
- Wait, Mr. Poj!

508
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:13,600
Don't do this.

509
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:16,600
So, you didn't take the bait, huh?

510
00:37:16,680 --> 00:37:18,560
You sly old fox!

511
00:37:18,640 --> 00:37:20,920
What are you standing there for? Get him!

512
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:22,760
Get that Thatri.

513
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:26,120
- Hey!
- Don't. Tri!

514
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:32,240
What?

515
00:37:32,920 --> 00:37:33,960
Where is he?

516
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:43,160
Look.

517
00:38:01,080 --> 00:38:03,600
Spread out. Find the guy

518
00:38:03,680 --> 00:38:05,240
and beat him to a pulp.

519
00:38:16,160 --> 00:38:17,080
Wild Bull?

520
00:38:17,160 --> 00:38:20,120
Yeah. What's up, Leopard?

521
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:23,000
Who are you beefing with now?

522
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:31,080
Still the same old charmer, Leopard?

523
00:38:31,160 --> 00:38:33,480
She's ready to ditch her husband
to run away with you.

524
00:38:35,160 --> 00:38:38,320
It's not funny. Her husband's
going to shoot me dead.

525
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:43,080
Hey.

526
00:38:43,160 --> 00:38:45,320
How many years has it been, Wild Bull?

527
00:38:46,160 --> 00:38:48,760
We were 16, so that's over ten years.

528
00:38:49,600 --> 00:38:51,560
Ever since you left for England.

529
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:54,320
I was stuck with exams back then

530
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:57,240
and couldn't make it to see you off.
I still regret that.

531
00:38:58,360 --> 00:38:59,800
Whoa. You remember all that?

532
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,240
Of course I do.

533
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:04,200
We were both named Thatri

534
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:06,040
and in the same class.

535
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:09,600
The guys had to give us nicknames
just to tell us apart.

536
00:39:09,680 --> 00:39:12,720
It's not every day you meet someone
with the same name, you know.

537
00:39:13,480 --> 00:39:14,480
So it made an impression?

538
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:15,880
Partly.

539
00:39:17,280 --> 00:39:20,600
You did me a huge favor back then.
How could I ever forget you?

540
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:23,160
So what if he's poor?
You have no right to bully him.

541
00:39:23,240 --> 00:39:24,600
Go pick on someone your own size.

542
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:29,200
Hey. Don't gang up.

543
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:30,400
I don't care.

544
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:31,720
Careful!

545
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:39,640
Don't just stand there. Learn your lesson.

546
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:42,960
Next one, step up.

547
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:49,600
It's not that sore.

548
00:39:50,280 --> 00:39:52,400
You didn't feel enough pain
from fighting, did you?

549
00:39:55,360 --> 00:39:56,480
Fighting that jerk

550
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:58,320
wasn't half as painful as that cane.

551
00:39:58,400 --> 00:39:59,960
That teacher is brutal.

552
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,840
I'm sorry, man.

553
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:05,080
You got beaten because of me.

554
00:40:05,160 --> 00:40:07,000
Don't apologize.

555
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:08,320
We're friends,

556
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,160
we share the same name,

557
00:40:10,240 --> 00:40:11,840
and we're on the same rugby team.

558
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:16,080
Besides,

559
00:40:16,160 --> 00:40:17,840
I can't stand bullies

560
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:21,040
who look down on others.

561
00:40:23,480 --> 00:40:24,640
Thanks, man.

562
00:40:26,080 --> 00:40:29,040
Let's go get something to eat.
I'm craving some Western food.

563
00:40:31,640 --> 00:40:34,200
It's too expensive. I'm broke.

564
00:40:35,040 --> 00:40:37,960
My treat. Don't overthink it. Let's go.

565
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:40,360
Alright? Let's go.

566
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:45,720
Thanks, man, for not looking
down on me back then.

567
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:47,280
Why would I?

568
00:40:47,360 --> 00:40:49,320
We're all human.

569
00:40:54,240 --> 00:40:56,200
So, what did you do after graduation?

570
00:40:57,720 --> 00:40:59,800
I got into university,

571
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:03,200
but I couldn't afford the tuition,
so I took a job in Nakhon Sawan

572
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:05,400
as a junior official.

573
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:10,600
But guess what?
I'm about to become a rich man.

574
00:41:10,680 --> 00:41:13,240
- A rich man?
- Yes.

575
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:16,920
I'm inheriting a fortune from my uncle.
He's a wealthy man in Phuket.

576
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:19,520
It's a long story.

577
00:41:20,120 --> 00:41:22,520
Well… my mother

578
00:41:22,600 --> 00:41:24,000
was supposed to inherit it,

579
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:27,000
but she refused.
She was furious at him and the relatives.

580
00:41:27,080 --> 00:41:28,960
So, she told me to take it instead.

581
00:41:29,040 --> 00:41:30,360
So, I've got--

582
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:43,960
We've got to move, Wild Bull.

583
00:42:42,160 --> 00:42:45,320
Help me, please!

584
00:42:45,400 --> 00:42:48,080
‪Help me!

585
00:42:58,400 --> 00:42:59,800
Are you okay?

586
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:02,240
Wild Bull!

587
00:43:03,680 --> 00:43:04,520
Wild Bull!

588
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:10,880
Wild Bull.

589
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:12,600
Hang in there.

590
00:43:12,680 --> 00:43:14,400
I'll take you to the hospital.

591
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:17,760
My suitcase. Where is it?

592
00:43:21,120 --> 00:43:22,560
My suitcase…

593
00:43:34,360 --> 00:43:35,520
Wild Bull.

594
00:43:37,600 --> 00:43:38,400
Wild Bull.

595
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:48,320
PENANG

596
00:44:02,120 --> 00:44:04,600
So, how does it feel,
our future millionaire?

597
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:08,040
In just a few days, she'll be off
to Phuket to claim that inheritance.

598
00:44:08,120 --> 00:44:11,200
I'm honestly so thrilled for her!

599
00:44:11,280 --> 00:44:14,240
We'll have a pretty and rich friend.

600
00:44:24,160 --> 00:44:27,280
I'm fine. I just miss my grandfather.

601
00:44:44,160 --> 00:44:45,480
Rajit.

602
00:44:46,840 --> 00:44:50,800
I know you hate my guts,
but I have something to tell you.

603
00:44:53,120 --> 00:44:56,160
As soon as I graduate,
I'm marrying Kajorn.

604
00:45:01,640 --> 00:45:02,680
Congratulations.

605
00:45:02,760 --> 00:45:03,840
Thanks.

606
00:45:04,360 --> 00:45:06,840
I did what I did
because I love him so much.

607
00:45:09,960 --> 00:45:11,440
Why are you telling me this?

608
00:45:13,680 --> 00:45:15,720
Men like him

609
00:45:15,800 --> 00:45:18,040
are a dime a dozen.

610
00:45:18,960 --> 00:45:20,520
If you want him, he's all yours.

611
00:45:24,160 --> 00:45:25,200
- Oops.
- Oops.

612
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:27,520
That's harsh.

613
00:45:27,600 --> 00:45:29,280
I bet it stings.

614
00:45:30,840 --> 00:45:32,800
- Are you okay?
- It stings.

615
00:45:37,080 --> 00:45:39,920
If he's really that pathetic,

616
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:42,640
why were you with him for so many years?

617
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:47,880
And this dried rose,
isn't that from him too?

618
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:57,280
If only I had known back then
that he was nothing but garbage,

619
00:46:00,840 --> 00:46:02,760
I would've tossed it out ages ago.

620
00:46:09,160 --> 00:46:10,240
Rajit…

621
00:46:25,640 --> 00:46:28,040
I told myself I'd be strong,

622
00:46:28,640 --> 00:46:30,320
but I just can't.

623
00:46:31,000 --> 00:46:33,200
Yes, you can.

624
00:46:33,800 --> 00:46:36,080
You were so brave back there.

625
00:46:38,200 --> 00:46:41,440
Why does everything
have to happen all at once?

626
00:46:41,520 --> 00:46:45,440
First Kajorn, and now my grandfather…

627
00:46:45,520 --> 00:46:47,400
If you need to cry,

628
00:46:48,040 --> 00:46:49,240
just let it all out.

629
00:46:50,280 --> 00:46:53,400
Crying isn't a sign of weakness.

630
00:46:54,320 --> 00:46:57,080
It's just how we acknowledge our pain.

631
00:47:04,000 --> 00:47:06,120
There's no need to hide your feelings.

632
00:47:06,760 --> 00:47:08,160
You're with us now.

633
00:47:09,000 --> 00:47:10,760
You can cry for as long as you need.

634
00:47:31,360 --> 00:47:34,720
BANGKOK NOI HOSPITAL

635
00:47:40,240 --> 00:47:41,080
You really

636
00:47:41,160 --> 00:47:43,560
are tough as a bull, aren't you?

637
00:47:44,160 --> 00:47:45,480
Of course I am.

638
00:47:45,560 --> 00:47:47,360
I'm not dying until I'm a rich man.

639
00:47:49,640 --> 00:47:51,600
Broken leg, cracked ribs,

640
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:54,320
but that mouth is still working just fine.

641
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:00,800
Where's my suitcase?

642
00:48:02,040 --> 00:48:04,080
Right here. What's in it?

643
00:48:04,760 --> 00:48:05,880
You've been obsessed.

644
00:48:05,960 --> 00:48:07,280
It's got the documents.

645
00:48:07,360 --> 00:48:10,040
I need them to prove my identity
and claim the inheritance.

646
00:48:11,520 --> 00:48:14,400
Wait until you're back on your feet.
Then you can go wherever you want.

647
00:48:14,480 --> 00:48:16,480
I can't wait.

648
00:48:25,400 --> 00:48:27,080
Leopard,

649
00:48:27,160 --> 00:48:30,600
I need you to do me one more favor.

650
00:48:31,560 --> 00:48:32,600
Spit it out, man.

651
00:48:33,400 --> 00:48:36,360
Before I head off to Chiang Mai,
tell me what you need.

652
00:48:38,640 --> 00:48:41,760
I need you to go to Phuket
and claim the inheritance in my place.

653
00:48:41,840 --> 00:48:44,480
Hey. Are you crazy?

654
00:48:44,560 --> 00:48:46,200
Pretending to be you?

655
00:48:46,280 --> 00:48:47,560
That's a one-way ticket to jail.

656
00:48:48,200 --> 00:48:51,040
You're overreacting. It's my fortune.

657
00:48:51,120 --> 00:48:54,400
You're just picking it up for me.
How is that a crime?

658
00:48:54,480 --> 00:48:56,400
Then why don't you
just go get it yourself?

659
00:48:57,000 --> 00:49:00,560
Open my bag. Read the letter inside,

660
00:49:01,240 --> 00:49:02,880
and then you'll understand.

661
00:49:14,560 --> 00:49:17,080
TO THATRI VORAPAT

662
00:49:27,600 --> 00:49:30,120
"You have to claim the inheritance
within seven days.

663
00:49:30,200 --> 00:49:33,480
Otherwise, it's considered
an automatic forfeiture."

664
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:35,760
I've only got two days.

665
00:49:38,360 --> 00:49:40,400
Look at me.

666
00:49:42,080 --> 00:49:45,480
I don't even know
if I'll be able to walk in two months.

667
00:49:47,240 --> 00:49:48,520
Please, help me.

668
00:49:49,040 --> 00:49:50,320
You know

669
00:49:50,400 --> 00:49:52,640
how poor my family is.

670
00:49:53,600 --> 00:49:57,520
Since my father died, it's been
a nightmare for my mother and me.

671
00:49:57,600 --> 00:50:01,360
If we get this,
she can finally live in peace.

672
00:50:04,160 --> 00:50:06,120
I'm begging you, Leopard.

673
00:50:06,200 --> 00:50:07,880
Help me out one last time.

674
00:50:12,080 --> 00:50:14,600
Do you think it's that easy
to just pretend to be you?

675
00:50:14,680 --> 00:50:16,320
Won't anyone get suspicious?

676
00:50:16,960 --> 00:50:18,680
No one has ever seen my face.

677
00:50:18,760 --> 00:50:20,200
Even Uncle Som,

678
00:50:21,040 --> 00:50:22,240
we've never met.

679
00:50:22,840 --> 00:50:26,560
All I have is the lawyer's letter
as proof of who I am.

680
00:50:27,400 --> 00:50:29,800
If you take this letter
and present yourself,

681
00:50:29,880 --> 00:50:31,400
no one will doubt you.

682
00:50:33,720 --> 00:50:36,120
It's not going to be that simple,
Wild Bull.

683
00:50:41,520 --> 00:50:42,680
I'm begging you.

684
00:50:43,800 --> 00:50:47,160
I have no other choice.
I have to take this risk.

685
00:50:47,240 --> 00:50:48,480
Please, friend?

686
00:50:50,360 --> 00:50:53,520
Once the will is read
and the assets are transferred,

687
00:50:53,600 --> 00:50:55,240
you can just leave.

688
00:50:56,240 --> 00:50:57,440
When I'm healed,

689
00:50:57,520 --> 00:50:58,840
I'll step forward myself.

690
00:50:58,920 --> 00:51:01,640
If there's any trouble,
I'll take the heat.

691
00:51:01,720 --> 00:51:03,520
I won't let you get dragged into it.

692
00:51:13,960 --> 00:51:17,040
PHANG NGA PIER

693
00:51:19,000 --> 00:51:22,360
The boat to Phuket
is about to leave. Hurry up!

694
00:51:39,400 --> 00:51:40,760
Excuse me.

695
00:51:40,840 --> 00:51:42,680
How many more hours until we reach Phuket?

696
00:51:48,920 --> 00:51:50,800
Why is everyone staring at me like that?

697
00:51:50,880 --> 00:51:52,880
What are you doing in Phuket?

698
00:51:53,520 --> 00:51:57,040
You don't look like a local.
What's your business there?

699
00:51:57,640 --> 00:51:58,960
What are you doing in Phuket?

700
00:52:00,080 --> 00:52:02,240
Could you speak standard Thai?
I don't understand.

701
00:52:03,800 --> 00:52:06,600
Could he be a pirate? He looks suspicious.

702
00:52:06,680 --> 00:52:09,040
Should we throw him overboard
and interrogate him later?

703
00:52:10,040 --> 00:52:12,720
What pirate would just
board a boat like this?

704
00:52:13,320 --> 00:52:14,680
Stop being so paranoid.

705
00:52:14,760 --> 00:52:16,720
So, what exactly
are you going to Phuket for?

706
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:18,040
Oh.

707
00:52:18,120 --> 00:52:19,760
I'm here to visit a relative.

708
00:52:19,840 --> 00:52:21,560
His name is Mr. Som,

709
00:52:21,640 --> 00:52:23,080
the owner of the Som Song Saeng residence.

710
00:52:27,000 --> 00:52:28,440
- Ah!
- Ah!

711
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:31,280
The pirates are here! Take cover!

712
00:52:32,960 --> 00:52:35,000
I'm dead. I'm absolutely dead.

713
00:52:35,080 --> 00:52:36,560
I was supposed
to be farming in Chiang Mai.

714
00:52:36,640 --> 00:52:38,760
Looks like I'm going to end up
a ghost here instead.

715
00:52:40,160 --> 00:52:43,360
Strip them of all their supplies
and valuables.

716
00:52:43,440 --> 00:52:45,840
Don't leave a thing behind! Open fire!

717
00:52:51,360 --> 00:52:52,400
No! The dog.

718
00:52:57,320 --> 00:52:58,680
Keep shooting!

719
00:53:01,080 --> 00:53:03,120
Give me that. You can't hit a thing.

720
00:53:23,560 --> 00:53:24,960
Hey. Retreat!

721
00:53:41,720 --> 00:53:44,080
Excuse me. Is there a vet around here?

722
00:53:44,160 --> 00:53:45,320
I don't know.

723
00:53:47,120 --> 00:53:49,680
Sorry, auntie. Is there
a vet clinic anywhere nearby?

724
00:53:49,760 --> 00:53:50,640
No idea.

725
00:53:54,200 --> 00:53:56,680
Hang in there, buddy.
I'm going to save you.

726
00:53:58,440 --> 00:54:00,960
Looking for a doctor, are ya?

727
00:54:20,200 --> 00:54:21,480
How is it, Doc?

728
00:54:21,560 --> 00:54:24,200
I got the bullet out.

729
00:54:28,160 --> 00:54:30,520
- Are you okay, Doc?
- Who?

730
00:54:30,600 --> 00:54:31,960
Me?

731
00:54:32,600 --> 00:54:33,960
Or that dog?

732
00:54:35,880 --> 00:54:37,040
If you're asking about me,

733
00:54:37,760 --> 00:54:38,600
I'm fine.

734
00:54:39,520 --> 00:54:42,520
But the dog? I've got no clue.

735
00:54:43,720 --> 00:54:45,440
I only ever treat people.

736
00:54:45,520 --> 00:54:48,040
This is my first time operating on a dog.

737
00:54:55,120 --> 00:54:56,080
DOCTOR SOMSAK
GENERAL MEDICINE

738
00:54:58,880 --> 00:55:00,560
Something on your mind?

739
00:55:01,760 --> 00:55:03,400
I really need to get
to my relative's place.

740
00:55:04,960 --> 00:55:08,080
Where is it?
Want me to have someone take you?

741
00:55:09,360 --> 00:55:12,240
I don't actually know.
I've never been there before.

742
00:55:12,320 --> 00:55:13,360
What?

743
00:55:13,440 --> 00:55:16,160
I only know his name is Mr. Som,

744
00:55:16,240 --> 00:55:17,800
a wealthy man in Phuket.

745
00:55:18,760 --> 00:55:20,000
His residence is called

746
00:55:20,920 --> 00:55:22,160
Som Song Saeng residence.

747
00:55:27,280 --> 00:55:28,920
You're really going to that house?

748
00:55:43,920 --> 00:55:46,720
If he doesn't show up by midnight,
he forfeits everything, right?

749
00:55:47,480 --> 00:55:48,320
That's correct.

750
00:55:48,400 --> 00:55:51,120
If Mr. Thatri doesn't arrive
within the stipulated time,

751
00:55:51,200 --> 00:55:53,400
he automatically forfeits
Mr. Som's inheritance.

752
00:55:55,600 --> 00:55:57,600
There's only one hour left.

753
00:55:57,680 --> 00:55:59,240
Do you think he'll make it?

754
00:56:00,240 --> 00:56:02,240
He won't make it. I've already checked.

755
00:56:02,320 --> 00:56:04,200
The last boat arrived at six.

756
00:56:04,280 --> 00:56:06,800
Look at the time. He's not here.

757
00:56:06,880 --> 00:56:08,040
No way he's going to make it.

758
00:56:10,120 --> 00:56:11,320
I still can't believe

759
00:56:11,400 --> 00:56:14,960
he'd just walk away
from such a massive fortune.

760
00:56:15,840 --> 00:56:17,360
Maybe he's just ashamed.

761
00:56:17,440 --> 00:56:20,320
He knows his mother
was a product of an affair.

762
00:56:20,400 --> 00:56:22,400
It's better he didn't
have the nerve to be here.

763
00:56:22,480 --> 00:56:24,680
- Pae, stop.
- What?

764
00:56:24,760 --> 00:56:28,160
I'm just stating the facts.
Don't go playing the saint, Fuang.

765
00:56:34,640 --> 00:56:35,720
Pae…

766
00:56:35,800 --> 00:56:38,520
The power just went out like that.
Do you think Uncle Som is angry

767
00:56:38,600 --> 00:56:40,880
because we were badmouthing his nephew?

768
00:56:43,680 --> 00:56:45,360
Ghosts?

769
00:56:45,440 --> 00:56:46,760
Don't be ridiculous.

770
00:56:47,280 --> 00:56:48,440
Vijarn.

771
00:56:49,400 --> 00:56:51,240
Go check the generator.

772
00:56:51,840 --> 00:56:52,640
Will do.

773
00:57:03,680 --> 00:57:05,320
Is this Som Song Saeng residence?

774
00:57:11,480 --> 00:57:13,360
Ah!

775
00:57:13,440 --> 00:57:14,520
- Ah!
- Ah!

776
00:57:15,360 --> 00:57:17,320
- Pae?
- Are you

777
00:57:17,400 --> 00:57:19,760
- Mr. Thatri?
- Yes.

778
00:57:20,800 --> 00:57:21,960
I'm Thatri.

779
00:57:23,240 --> 00:57:24,840
A letter? That's it?

780
00:57:24,920 --> 00:57:26,480
How do we even know you're the real deal?

781
00:57:27,640 --> 00:57:29,760
Thief! There's a thief in the house!

782
00:57:31,480 --> 00:57:32,600
Ah!

783
00:57:32,680 --> 00:57:35,040
That arrogant guy you were badmouthing

784
00:57:35,120 --> 00:57:36,520
is your uncle?

785
00:57:36,600 --> 00:57:38,960
Who would've thought
the world was this small?

786
00:57:39,040 --> 00:57:41,240
And now we have to live
under the same roof as relatives.

787
00:57:41,320 --> 00:57:42,160
Uncle Ree?

788
00:57:43,880 --> 00:57:46,360
What are you doing?

789
00:57:47,600 --> 00:57:49,040
I promise,

790
00:57:49,120 --> 00:57:52,400
I will take the best care of your fortune.

791
00:57:52,480 --> 00:57:54,400
I've been authorized by the authorities

792
00:57:54,480 --> 00:57:56,000
to take down Zhang Gong Cheng.

793
00:57:56,080 --> 00:57:59,360
<i>He's a pirate, terrorizing these waters,</i>
<i>causing chaos everywhere.</i>

794
00:57:59,440 --> 00:58:01,360
What does that have to do
with Som Song Saeng residence?

795
00:58:30,680 --> 00:58:32,680
Subtitle translation by:
Khathathong Thongtumlueng
